Walker Telecommunications Corpsaid the company has decided to discontinue operations of itsMobile Communications Division which will result in a one-timesubstantial loss for the fourth quarter and year.    For the fourth quarter and year ended December 31, 1985Walker reported a net loss of 17,000 dlrs and net income of175,000, respectively.    Walker said retail prices for mobile cellular telephoneshave declined dramatically to point where the company no longerbelieves that it can profitably participate in the market. Reuter&#3;